data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` construction **won't compile**. Replace the entire block:

```csharp
// EF Core 10 — simple lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more expression tree gymnastics — `ExecuteUpdateAsync` accepts `Action<SetPropertyCalls<Blog>>` now.

---

### 2. Complex type column naming changes (two issues)

**Same-named properties across complex types** are now uniquified (e.g., `Street` → `Street1`). **Nested complex types** now use the full path (`Complex_NestedComplex_Property` instead of `NestedComplex_Property`).

Both changes generate migrations that rename columns. Pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested: Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City
// Was:    BillingAddress_City
// Now:    Payment_BillingAddress_City
// Pin it:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, a =>
        {
            a.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on this interface gained a `string logCommandText` parameter. Your implementation won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL safe for logging
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
